{"name":"Xenosavant","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"In his study and prosecution of the xenos threat, the Acolyte has become well-versed in the ways and forms of the myriad alien races that menace humanity. The character can attempt any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 3 in Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"xenosavant","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge, investigation","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0Dxu1IpkaHvEacT3"}
{"name":"Leaping Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The Acolyte has become practiced at escaping weapons that cover an area to deadly effect, from flamers to strange xenos devices. When he would make an Agility test to avoid attacks from weapons with the Spray quality, he may make the test using his Dodge (Ag) skill instead.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Agility 35, Rank 2 in the Dodge skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"leapingdodge","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"defence, dodge","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6Dp9jwRiRsws0P3O"}
{"name":"Field Vivisection","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The Acolyte is well-versed in the blasphemous anatomy of his xenos foes, and uses this knowledge to utmost effect, both in the laboratorium and on the battlefield. Each time this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair (Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When using the Called Shot action with a melee or ranged attack (depending on the Specialisation) against a target for which the character has the appropriate Forbidden Lore (Xenos) skill, he makes a Medicae (WS) or Medicae (BS) test in place of the normal Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill test.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill 40, Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any), Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"Ranged, Melee","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"fieldvivisection","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"range, melee","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BlKcc04ujIwrMx3W"}
{"name":"Skilled Rider","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Often, the best way to overcome the heretic is with merciless speed, and so many Acolytes make extensive use of vehicles and mounts in their pursuit of humanity's enemies. Whether the character has used his prized bike until it feels like an extension of his own body, or he has the experience necessary to instantly adjust to the strange mounts and vehicles found across the Askellon Sector, moving to or from the saddle or pilot's seat is second nature. Whenever the character would be thrown from or tossed about within his vehicle, he makes an Ordinary (+10) Agility test. If he succeeds, the character may choose to either land safely on his feet or retain in his original position in the vehicle. In addition, once per round the character can attempt an Ordinary (+10) Agility test to Mount or Dismount a vehicle as a Free Action.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in any Operate skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"skilledrider","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FmWs0fIICSmJY0fA"}
{"name":"Weapon Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"In the prosecution of his duties against the alien, the Acolyte wields the most arcane and rare weapons the Adeptus Mechanicus can craft, and perhaps even takes up the very armaments of the xenos to better combat it. From years of experience, the character can quickly discern the firing mechanisms and balance of even the strangest weapons, regardless of its origin. The character reduces the penalty for using a weapon without the proper training by 10.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Exotic Weapon Training (Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"weaponintuition","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"combat","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GQfU0CJE02Du7dM1"}
{"name":"Lexographer","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"From years poring over dusty tomes and examining ancient ruins on forgotten worlds&mdash;and perhaps even speaking face-to- face with inhuman beings&mdash;the Acolyte has become an expert in deciphering lost human languages as well as those of xenos. The character can attempt any Linguistics skill in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 3 in Linguistics (Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"lexographer","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge, research","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Np0N7Z7WuysXEkwF"}
{"name":"Ambassador Imperialis","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Whether from serving in the fleet of a Rogue Trader or dealing with xenos mercenaries on frontier worlds, the Acolyte is experienced in dealing with alien and the most divergent of non- Imperial cultures, able to avoid the subtle faux pas that can so easily cause a negotiation to deteriorate into bloodshed. The character reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20. In addition, once per encounter, he can reroll a failed Interaction skill test when interacting with such an NPC.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Fellowship 35, Intelligence 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Social","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"ambassadorimperialis","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fellowship, investigation","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QtJwjuYGPDe6uVlX"}
{"name":"Hotshot Pilot","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"When the situation calls for it, the opeator stretches the bounds of his abilities, displaying impressive feats of manoeuvring. This experience has also taught the Acolyte how to recover from what might become fatal mishaps for a less skilled operator attempting such manoeuvres. When the Acolyte succeeds on an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue to add a number of degrees of success equal to half of his Agility bonus. When the Acolyte fails an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue in order to reduce the degrees of failure by an amount equal to his Agility bonus, to a minimum of 1.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Agility 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hotshotpilot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RPhrmOi3IfbXfmxA"}
{"name":"Hull Down","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The Acolyte remains aware of his foes at all times in combat, carefully angling his vehicle or steed at each moment to present a narrower silhouette to all attackers, as well as taking the best advantage of any intervening terrain to gain cover. When the character takes a vehicle combat action with the Movement subtype, his vehicle or steed counts the value of its Size trait as being one lower for purposes of attack modifiers and the benefits of cover until the start of his next turn.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hulldown","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UjsnVbisZAyhcyKD"}
{"name":"Push the Limit","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Whether through study, practice, or sheer intuition, the Acolyte is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed, and knows how to push it to those limits and beyond. Although overtaxing a beast or executing wheel-tearing turns can provide a great advantage in combat or pursuit, a single wrong move can prove catastrophic, injuring the pilot or even ripping his vehicle apart. Once per round, the character may add +20 to an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of living steeds); however, if he fails the test by 4 or more degrees of failure, immediately roll 1d5 on Table 7-32: Motive Systems Critical Hit Effects on page 257 of the D ark h ErEsy Core Rulebook and apply the result. If he is riding a living mount, roll 1d5 on Table 7-18: Impact Critical Effects - Leg on page 239 of the D ark h ErEsy Core Rulebook and apply the result.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Tech-Use","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"pushthelimit","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VqQePW8jtqoWwNWe"}
{"name":"Archivator","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Whether through years of experience or specialised training, the Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperium's countless archives. From delving into deep info-crypts to searching mouldering librarium stacks and deciphering ancient tech-slabs, the Acolyte can uncover knowledge thought long lost. When making a Scholastic Lore or Forbidden Lore test utilising sources of recorded information of any sort, such as cogitators, tomes, info-nets, and data-slates, the character can re- roll a failed test once with a -10 penalty. In addition, tests to perform research or find information in these circumstances take half the usual time.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Int 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Knowledge, Perception","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"archivator","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Y84AWtWpuCyA2FG6"}
{"name":"Grenadier","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The Acolyte knows that grenades and other explosives are amongst the most effective ways to bring down marauding alien beasts, or to quickly thin out hordes of lesser xenos monstrosities. When the character misses with a thrown weapon or weapon with the Blast quality, he may reduce the distance it scatters by a number of metres up to half his BS bonus.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ballistic Skill 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"grenadier","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"range","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qtjAG0XD430UK2Xq"}
